## Step #3: Install a Management Server
In this step, we will configure a Stack Automation management server that will execute, manage and monitor the Kubernetes workload we discovered and plan to deploy.

1. In the "Connect a Management Server" dialog, select the __"Install new self-hosted management server"__ and click "Next". Now, you are required to choose one of the supported cloud providers managed Kubernetes service or a self-managed Kubernetes cluster. Choose one of the options, In this example, we will use AWS EKS.
2. Provide a new for the management server, and click "Next"
3. Click on "Generate", this will generate a CLI command based on ```kubectl``` that you can now execute on the Kubernetes cluster. Here is an example output of the command. 


